        "subject": "LU-930 doc: align lfs and lctl man page structure",
        "message": "LU-930 doc: align lfs and lctl man page structure\n\nBring the lfs.1 and lctl.8 man page structure into alignment.\nList the general usage description first, then common commands,\nand top-level command-line options, before the command list.\n\nAdd a bash-completion section so that users can learn about\nthis useful functionality.\n\nReorder command listing to be in more alphabetical order.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nChange-Id: I5f738bb37b77f6cc0789071d7573320eda500c1e\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64404\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nReviewed-by: Frederick Dilger <fdilger@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
